<exercise checkit-seed="0030" checkit-slug="E1" checkit-title="Linear systems, vector equations, and augmented matrices">
  <statement>
    <p> Consider the system of equations
            <md alignment="alignat" alignat-columns=" 4 "><mrow>x &amp;-&amp; 2 \, y &amp;-&amp; z &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow><mrow> &amp; &amp; y &amp;+&amp; z &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow><mrow>-2 \, x &amp;+&amp; 7 \, y &amp;+&amp; 5 \, z &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow><mrow>2 \, x &amp;-&amp; 5 \, y &amp;-&amp; 3 \, z &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow></md></p>
    <ol>
      <li> Write an augmented matrix corresponding to this system. </li>
      <li> Write a vector equation corresponding to this system. </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; -2 &amp; -1 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\
-2 &amp; 7 &amp; 5 &amp; 0 \\
2 &amp; -5 &amp; -3 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me> x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
0 \\
-2 \\
2
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
1 \\
7 \\
-5
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-1 \\
1 \\
5 \\
-3
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
0 \\
0 \\
0 \\
0
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

